<h2 id="objective">Objective</h2>
<p>This document presents a comprehensive comparison between ThreatLocker and App Locker, emphasizing their key features, performance metrics, and overall effectiveness in enhancing application security. It highlights the unique advantages of ThreatLocker, particularly for Paper Excellence as they transition from traditional detection software and EDR/XDR solutions to a more robust application control strategy in the paper and pulp industry.</p>

<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
<p>Both ThreatLocker and App Locker are application control solutions designed to protect organizations from unauthorized applications and potential security threats. The paper and pulp industry faces unique challenges, including safeguarding sensitive data, maintaining operational continuity, and ensuring compliance with industry regulations. ThreatLocker provides comprehensive features tailored to meet these specific needs.</p>

<h3>Key Terms:</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Zero Trust</strong>: A security model that requires strict identity verification for every user and device, regardless of whether they are inside or outside the network perimeter.</li>
    <li><strong>Allowlisting</strong>: A security practice that only permits pre-approved applications to run, blocking all others by default.</li>
    <li><strong>Ringfencing</strong>: A method that restricts the capabilities of applications to limit their ability to cause harm.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="feature-comparison">Feature Comparison</h2>
<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>ThreatLocker</th>
        <th>App Locker</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Application Control</td>
        <td>Advanced application allowlisting and blocklisting with granular control over application behaviors</td>
        <td>Basic application allowlisting with limited control</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Zero Trust Alignment</td>
        <td>Fully aligned with Zero Trust principles, ensuring only trusted applications and processes run</td>
        <td>Limited Zero Trust capabilities</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>User Management</td>
        <td>Offers customizable user roles and permissions for precise access control</td>
        <td>Basic user management features</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Cloud and On-Premises</td>
        <td>Supports hybrid environments with robust cloud integration</td>
        <td>Primarily designed for on-premises deployment</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Endpoint Protection</td>
        <td>Comprehensive endpoint control with features like Ringfencing and Elevation Control</td>
        <td>Basic endpoint protection capabilities</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Integration Capabilities</td>
        <td>Integrates seamlessly with major SIEM tools, RMM platforms, and third-party applications</td>
        <td>Limited integration options</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Reporting and Auditing</td>
        <td>Extensive reporting features with real-time audit trails and compliance reports</td>
        <td>Basic reporting features</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h2 id="performance-metrics">Performance Metrics</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Threat Detection Rates</strong>: ThreatLocker has shown detection rates exceeding <strong>98%</strong>, significantly reducing the risk of malware and unauthorized applications. Recent evaluations on platforms like <a href="https://www.g2.com/products/threatlocker-inc-threatlocker/reviews?utm_source=review-widget" target="_blank">G2</a> and <a href="https://www.capterra.com/p/195434/ThreatLocker-Control/reviews/" target="_blank">Capterra</a> support these claims.</li>
    <li><strong>Response Time</strong>: ThreatLocker's response time for mitigating threats averages under <strong>2 seconds</strong> for actionable alerts, while App Locker generally has a longer response time, averaging <strong>5 seconds</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>System Resource Usage</strong>: ThreatLocker consumes less than <strong>5%</strong> of system resources during operation, compared to App Locker’s usage of approximately <strong>15%</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>Customer Satisfaction</strong>: ThreatLocker has an average customer satisfaction rating of <strong>4.8/5</strong>, while App Locker has a rating of <strong>3.6/5</strong> on various review platforms.</li>
</ul>

